claims:
1. A process for catalytically transforming a natural gas liquid (NGL) into one or more higher molecular weight hydrocarbons, comprising:
providing a hydrocarbon containing gas stream comprising one or more light alkanes chosen from the group consisting of C2, C3, C4, C5, and combinations thereof;
catalytically dehydrogenating at least a portion of the light alkanes to corresponding alkene derivatives using at least one bimetallic catalyst;
catalytically oligomerizing at least a portion of the alkenes to provide one or more higher molecular weight hydrocarbons; and
recovering the higher molecular weight hydrocarbons.

17. A process for catalytically transforming a natural gas liquid (NGL) into one or more higher molecular weight hydrocarbons, comprising:
providing a hydrocarbon containing gas stream comprising one or more light alkanes chosen from the group consisting of C2, C3, C4, C5, and combinations thereof;
catalytically dehydrogenating at least a portion of the light alkanes to corresponding alkene derivatives using at least one bimetallic catalyst;
catalytically oligomerizing at least a portion of the alkenes in the presence of at least one oligomerization catalyst to provide one or more higher molecular weight hydrocarbons; and
recovering the higher molecular weight hydrocarbons, wherein the at least one oligomerization catalyst comprises H-ZSM-5, B,Al-H-ZSM-5, nickel, iron, cobalt, or combinations thereof.

22. A process for catalytically transforming a natural gas liquid (NGL) into one or more higher molecular weight hydrocarbons, comprising:
providing a hydrocarbon containing gas stream that is derived from a shale formation, the stream comprising one or more light alkanes chosen from the group consisting of C2, C3, C4, C5, and combinations thereof;
catalytically dehydrogenating at least a portion of the light alkanes to corresponding alkene derivatives;
oligomerizing at least a portion of the alkenes in the presence of at least one oligomerization catalyst to provide one or more higher molecular weight hydrocarbons; and
recovering the higher molecular weight hydrocarbons,
wherein the at least one oligomerization catalyst comprises: a crystalline microporous zeolite structure having MFI topology; heteroatoms within the MFI structure selected from the group consisting of aluminum, gallium, iron and combinations thereof; and trivalent boron atoms within the MFI structure that have been substituted for tetravalent silicon atoms.
